# Admin UI (jsonConfig)

## Files

- `admin/jsonConfig.json` — UI definition (source of truth for labels/help)
- `admin/i18n/de.json`, `admin/i18n/en.json` — **manually maintained only**
- All other languages (`es`, `fr`, `it`, `nl`, `pl`, `pt`, `ru`, `uk`, `zh-cn`) — generated by owner via `npm run translate`; do **not** edit manually

## jsonConfig guidelines

- End-user friendly labels; tooltips for complex options
- Sensible defaults; validation on required fields (e.g. `interval` min 60)
- Images in `admin/img/`, referenced as `img/<filename>` in `staticImage` elements
- Every jsonConfig field must exist in `io-package.json` → `native` with a default

## Translations workflow

When changing `admin/jsonConfig.json`:

1. Add new keys to `admin/i18n/de.json` (German) and `admin/i18n/en.json` (English)
2. Remove orphaned keys from `de.json` and `en.json` when keys are removed from jsonConfig
3. Keys must match jsonConfig exactly; sort alphabetically
4. Do **not** run `npm run translate` — owner runs it before release

## Config fields

- `motionHost` (text): MotionEye server hostname or IP
- `motionEyePort` (number): config API port (default 8765)
- `motionPort` (number): Motion HTTP port (default 7999)
- `motionEyeUser` / `motionEyePassword`: MotionEye credentials
- `cameras` (array): per-camera config — table UI in Phase 1
